item.title: Silabsoft client won't load
item.dc:creator: @iceman327 iceman327
item.description:
@iceman327 wrote:

[quote=“surfer25, post:9, topic:148591”][quote author=EwfsPrince link=topic=203764.msg1797184#msg1797184 date=1191399327]

Ah i can’t remember how to set the ports…
could you refresh my memory please?
[/quote] You don’t set ports with clients on normal circumstances. I think you mean changing the server port then that would be a server question. Search the forum for the help you need on changing server ports.

author=deejaydyl8 link=topic=203764.msg1797183#msg1797183 date=1191399306]
Haha, you have to load Moparscape once.

He’s talking about the Silabsoft client not the mopar client.

Silab Run’s off The Mopar Cache[/quote]

yeah thanks for clarifying that…
I restored my computer so incidently all the files vanished
after I redownloaded moparscape client it worked.
